Female (
Holotype
, 
Brazil
, BMNH 1897.9.20.906-9). Total length 5.56. Carapace 2.82 long, 2.57 wide, light brown. Clypeus light brown, 0.32 high. Anterior eye row straight, 0.80 wide; posterior recurved, 1.24 wide. Eye diameters, interdistances, and median ocular quadrangle: AME 0.18, ALE 0.10, PME 0.21, PLE 0.20; AME-AME 0.09, AME-ALE 0.12, PME-PME 0.28, PME-PLE 0.16, OQA 0.40, OQP 0.66, OQH 0.42. Chelicerae orange, with scattered bristles. Sternum yellow, with scattered bristles; 1.36 long, 1.39 wide. Labium light brown, 0.34 long, 0.46 wide. Legs light brown, with dark brown annuli on femora; relative length: IV-II-I-III, I—femur 3.48/ patella-tibia 4.39/ metatarsus 3.73/ tarsus 1.66/ total 13.26; II—3.65/ 4.73/ 3.32/ 1.57/ 13.27; III—2.90/ 3.32/ 2.57/ 1.24/ 10.03; IV—4.06/ 4.98/ 4.15/ 1.90/ 15.09. Ventral pairs of macrosetae on tibiae: I-5; II-5; III-3; IV-4. Palpal tarsus claw with five teeth (
Fig. 48
). Superior tarsal claw with ten teeth, inferior with one tooth (
Fig. 49
). Trichobothrial hood smooth (
Fig. 50
). Dorsum of metatarsi with feathery setae (
Fig. 51
). Abdomen 2.73 long, light brown, with T-shaped patches on cardiac area and two pairs of sigillae. Venter light yellow, with scattered bristles. Middle field of the epigynum rugose and with conspicuous lateral lobes (
Fig. 44
). Copulatory duct 1 long and curved (
Fig. 45
). Head of spermathecae inconspicuous (
Fig. 45
); hood internally enlarged (
Fig. 46
).

