Fig. 10
). Sternum yellow, 1.50 long, 1.57 wide. Labium as in female, 0.41 long, 0.49 wide. Legs yellow, unmarked; relative length: I-II-IV-III, I—femur 6.30/ patella-tibia 8.54/ metatarsus 6.97/ tarsus 2.82/ total 24.63; II—6.05/ 7.88/ 7.05/ 2.90/ 23.88; III—4.39/ 5.31/ 3.98/ 1.74/ 15.42; IV—5.97/ 7.22/ 6.05/ 2.57/ 21.81. Ventral pairs of macrosetae on tibiae: I-5; II-5; III-3; IV-4. Abdomen 2.90 long, colouration as in female. Palpus with a rounded apex on the median apophysis and distal tegular projection short (
Fig. 52
). Retrolateral tibial apophysis with a subtriangular ventral branch, a finger-like ectal branch and an elongated ectal branch, with a lamellar base (
